               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en" source="#bibl000048x-2">The Sage Mother Hall, also known as the Holy Mother Hall, is the oldest building in the Jinci Shrine complex，as well as one of the most important surviving wooden structures in the  <term ref="/keyword/k000055">North Song Dynasty</term> . The building has undergone repeated restoration, it may first construct in the ninth year of Taiping Xingguo (太平興國) reign (984) of the <term ref="/keyword/k000055">North Song Dynasty</term>  (Chai 2000,11) and the current hall was likely built from 1038 to 1087 during the <term ref="/keyword/k000055">North Song Dynasty</term> (Miller 2007，122). Then the hall was repaired under imperial orders in the first year of the Chongning(崇寧) reign (1102)of the  <term ref="/keyword/k000055">North Song Dynasty</term> , later after Song Dynasty there were another five larger repairs. Until 1992, it was overhauled due to sinking foundations and tilting of the hall.(Chai 2000,15)Sage Mother Hall is located on the back of the Mountain Xuanwen. It is east-west oriented and the main entrance is facing the east, in front of which is the Fly Bridge. The hall with a double-eaves hip-and-gable roof is placed on a foundation platform, which measuring a front facade of 26.71 meters and side facades of 21.15 meters. The main body of the hall is five-bay across the front facade and eight-rafter along the side facades, which are surrounded by a second set of eaves covering a veranda that is one-bay (two-rafter) deeps along the side. It is characterized by cascading structures, the same as the diantang (palatial hall) configuration in Yingzao fashi. To create the four-rafter-deep ( 6.8 meters ) veranda along the front facade, four front columns of the central section in the central and second bays, are cut short and supported three-rafter beams of the front veranda. The cella is six-rafter deeps, roof frame of which is composed of through beams.
                  The 43 sculptures inside the hall are thought to be original works of the <term ref="/keyword/k000074">Song Dynasty</term>. In addition, the carved-wooden-dragon that coiled around eight lower-eave columns of the front facade is an isolated example of the <term ref="/keyword/k000074">Song Dynasty</term>. Structures of the surrounded veranda, sunlight barriers, and inter bracket-set boards are all covered with polychrome paintings or wall paintings. Plaque over the central bay of the core hall reads Sage Mother of Clear Efficacy and Manifest Aid (顯靈昭濟聖母). Locals will make some offerings with fruits and cakes for the hall is faces east, only in the early morning can the sunlight penetrate the front veranda and shine in front of the sculpture of Sage Mother in the cella. There are 30 stone monuments preserved in the surrounded veranda and 20 plaques of <term ref="/keyword/k000051">Ming </term> and <term ref="/keyword/k000070">Qing </term>dynasties hanging in the front veranda. (Southeast University Precision Mapping Project Team of Sage Mother Hall in Jin shrines, 2010-2012) </desc>            
               <desc type="builing-data" xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#bibl000048x-2">聖母殿是晉祠內現存時代最古的一座建築物，也是現存最重要的<term ref="/keyword/k000055">北宋</term>（960-1127）木構建築之一。殿初建於<term ref="/keyword/k000055">北宋</term> 太平興國九年(984年)（柴2000,11），今建築主體的建造年代約為1038-1087（Miller2007，122）。<term ref="/keyword/k000055">北宋</term>崇寧元年（1102）奉敕重修，宋以後還有五次較大的修繕。直至1992年，因基礎下沈，殿身傾斜等原因，聖母殿進行落架大修（柴2000，15）。
                  聖母殿背靠懸甕山，坐西向東，殿前為魚沼飛梁。殿坐於臺基上，通面闊26.71米，通進深21.15米。重檐九脊頂。殿身面闊五間，進深八架椽；副階周匝，副階進深一間（二椽）。殿身構架以層疊為特征，如《營造法式》之殿堂。為形成深四椽（6.8米）的寬闊前廊，殿身前檐當心間、次間檐柱不落地，立於三椽栿上。殿內部分深六椽，上架通梁。                 
                  殿內有彩塑43尊，多為宋代原塑。大殿正面八根下檐柱上有木制盤龍，為<term ref="/keyword/k000074">宋 Dynasty</term>代孤例。前廊與副階的木構架、障日板與栱眼壁均分布有彩畫或壁畫。殿身心間上懸匾額“顯靈昭濟聖母”。因大殿朝向東方，僅清晨陽光可透入前廊，照射於殿中聖母像前，本地人亦會以果餅等略加供奉。大殿副階中保存有石碑30通，前廊懸掛<term ref="/keyword/k000051">明 </term><term ref="/keyword/k000070">清</term>匾額20塊。（東南大學晉祠聖母殿精細測繪項目組，2010-2012）</desc>                             
